Wedit is a native LCC-Win32 port to Unix-like operating systems.

It features an user friendly IDE, project wizard, generation of GNU
makefiles and automake/autoconf skeletons, fast run-time source parsing
with syntax coloring and autoformating of C, Fortran, and Eiffel sources.

It also has complete analysis of source code and object files, many charts
and plots, and an integrated debugger.

WWW: http://www.q-software-solutions.com/weditlinux/index.shtml
